text.section:
The members shall include:
1 member of the Senate of Maryland appointed by the President of the Senate;
1 member of the Maryland House of Delegates appointed by the Speaker of the House;
at least 1 representative, appointed by the Secretary, from:
the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene;
the Governor's Office for Children, Youth, and Families;
the Head Start Program;
the State Department of Education;
the Office of the State Fire Marshal;
a local government;
a child care advocacy organization;
an independent school, which may include a religious, nonsectarian, or nursery school;
a child care resource and referral agency;
the Department of the Environment;
a community college with an early childhood education program;
the Maryland Association of Social Services Directors; and
a professional organization concerned with the quality of early childhood programs;
at least 1 representative, appointed by the State Superintendent, who is:
a local fire official who has responsibility for the enforcement or administration of fire codes;
a user of child care services; and
a business person;
a pediatrician with an interest and expertise in child care issues, appointed by the State Superintendent;
at least two family child care providers, appointed by the State Superintendent; and
at least two child care providers from child care centers, appointed by the State Superintendent.
